The paper deals with the detection of fiducial points on faces using machine learning, specifically convolutional networks. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses domain adaptation, which involves adapting a model trained on one domain to another domain. This is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with animal faces, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
